==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brant-fox
<hw>Brant"-fox`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>brand-fox</ets>; cf. G. <ets>brandfuchs</ets>, Sw.
<ets>bradr⟦aum⟧f</ets>. So called from its yellowish brown and somewhat
black color. See <er>Brand</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A kind
of fox found in Sweden (<spn>Vulpes alopex</spn>), smaller than the
common fox (<spn>Vulpes vulgaris</spn>), but probably a variety of
it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Branular</ent>⟦br⟧
